/**
 * @file README
 * @Synopsis joeltong.org - my personal vim configuration
 * @author TONG Haowen Joel.  Based off various links on net.
 * @version 1.0.1
 * @date 2012-05-26
 */

This is the Vim configuration I use.  It has been placed on GIT for easy
cloning.

Features the following plugins:
    - Pathogen         |For clarity and easy plugin add-ons
    - Addon-mw-utils   |Required for snipmate ver. 2 to function
    - align            |Align text based on tokens, useful for variable '=' alignment
    - autoclosetag     |to close tags automatically
    - autocomplpop     |Open omnicomplete prompt automatically when typing functions
    - bufexplorer      |Easily navigate between buffers using menu-like prompting
    - clang_complete   |for Cpp code completion without using ctags
    - delimitMate      |autocloses tags
    - doxygen-toolkit  |To easily create doxygen tags and license / author
    information
    - minibufexpl      |To easily control and share buffer tabs and data. another
    buffer explorer.
    - nerdcommenter    |Easily add comments
    - nerdtree         |File explorer in Vim
    - piv              |PHP integration for Vim
    - pyflakes         |Needed for python checking in syntastic to function
    - showmarks        |easily show marks made in vim
    - Snipmate-snippets|Snippets for snipmate.  snipmate depends on this.
    - Snipmate         |Add common codeblocks using only a few keystrokes
    - Supertab         |omnicomplete without pressing C-x C-o, just use tab key
    - surround         |replace brackets (any type) with ease
    - syntastic        |checks document syntax while saving
    - tagbar           |show list of functions in document
    - tasklist         |show tasklist TODO comments
    - tlib_vim         |needed for snipmate ver 2 to function.
    - Wombat           |The wombat color scheme.

INSTALLATION:
    1. To install, git clone git@github.com:toiletfreak/.vim.git as your .vim
    folder.  Or symlink to it.
    2. Symlink .vim/.vimrc to the location of your .vimrc
    3. install pyflakes.  This can be done in ubuntu with "sudo apt-get install
    pyflakes".
    4. start script.
    5. For additional shortcuts and help, look inside .vimrc and check the
    online documentation for each submodule.
